# Subagent Routing (clouds-f)

Canonical source: `references/subagent-registry.md`.

Use this rule when task scope benefits from specialized deep review, audit, or optimization in one domain.

## Routing Triggers

- Deep codebase tracing -> `code-explorer`
- Architecture blueprinting -> `code-architect`
- TS/JS strict review -> `typescript-reviewer`
- Type model and invariants -> `type-design-analyzer`
- Silent failures, swallowed errors, weak fallbacks -> `silent-failure-hunter`
- Cleanup and simplification -> `code-simplifier`
- Dead code removal campaign -> `refactor-cleaner`
- Performance bottleneck audits -> `performance-optimizer`
- Security review/hardening -> `security-reviewer`
- Security threat audit -> `security-auditor`
- SEO technical audits -> `seo-specialist`
- Final merge/readiness review -> `code-reviewer`

## Delegation Constraints

1. Keep subagent scope explicit (files/module/concern).
2. Do not delegate architecture-wide rewrites without user approval.
3. Preserve compatibility and existing behavior unless task says otherwise.
4. Record assumptions and unresolved risks in final summary.
